arts.ttl: Newport County AFC v Cheltenham Town RECAP: Robins' wait for away win ended in style
arts.sum: Goals from Matty Taylor, Ethan Williams and Ethon Archer secured Cheltenham Town's first away win in League Two since October 26 as Newport County AFC were blown away at Rodney Parade. Williams made it 2-0 eight minutes into the second half with the first goal of his senior career, lifting the ball into an empty net from 35 yards after goalkeeper Nick Townsend advanced from his penalty area and failed to clear his lines.

arts.ttl: Michael Flynn makes a winning return to Newport with Cheltenham
arts.sum: The Robins were convincing winners in south Wales.
